{
  "text": "Miscarriage is defined as a spontaneous loss of an intrauterine pregnancy before the fetus is able to survive independently. First trimester miscarriage is defined as \u2264 12 weeks gestation of miscarriage [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The occurrence of miscarriage was 10-20% in natural pregnant women, with 80% of pregnancy losses occurring in the first trimester [CITATION_3] . Studies had shown that the rate of miscarriage among in vitro fertilization and embryo transfer (IVF-ET) pregnant women was similar to that of natural pregnant women [CITATION_4] . A study showed that the miscarriage rate was 14.7% in 62,228 clinical pregnancies after IVF treatment in 1996-1998 in USA [CITATION_5] , which decreased to 9.5% in 2015 [CITATION_6] . A retrospective cohort study of 112,549 IVF cycles during 1999-2008 in the UK showed the miscarriage rate was 8.3% [CITATION_7] .",
